<br>
&quot;I am not an officer of Amnesty nor a representative of the Saryrn Guild Alliance, the following statements are and editorial by msyelf and are not official statements from either organizations.&quot;<br>
<br>
Recently, I was approached by a player who had grouped with Amnesty and SGA members in Icewell.  This individual said that everything was going along great, and then a Druid Spell dropped.  He asked if he could roll on this item, and was told that &quot;This was a guild raid&quot; and that &quot;it was guild property&quot;.  If this behavior wasn't bad enough, when an SGA cleric showed up, the druid was shown the door.  Told that he would have to leave the group to allow the cleric to join.  This individual couldn't remember any of the names specifically, otherwise I would be tearing these individuals apart verbally.<br>
<br>
I was appalled when I heard this.  This is exactly why I have pursued the SGA and done everything that I have to promote it.  I was sick and tired of the big guilds inviting people when they needed them and not letting them roll on loot.  Kicking them out of groups when another one of their members showed up.<br>
<br>
What happened to the ideals of the smaller guilds and such getting together to help others.  Do you all not remember what it was like when the bigger guilds treated us this way ?<br>
<br>
Another thing that has bothered me has been the cookie cutter response letters that other guilds have gotten when they have applied to join the SGA.  As far as I can discertain, nothing has been done to get these people into the SGA.<br>
<br>
Another thing that has bothered me as been the elitist attitude that I have seen.  People stating that they want an all SGA only raid.  Is this what we want ?  Again, do you not remember the feeling when other guilds like TWC and OOP and such told you that you could not attend their raids.  Wasn't this why the SGA was founded so we could do things.  And that other people would not be excluded no matter what guild they are in or if they were in a guild at all ?<br>
<br>
Some one please tell me if this is the path that the SGA is going to take, I would like to know.<br>
 <p>Hareq Ghoulslayer, 54 Paladin of Amnesty, Saryrn
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usarindal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sarindal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/16/01 9:21:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: State of the Union address</span><hr size=1> I agree wholeheartedly with your vision of the SGA Hareq - I'd MUCH rather see us working together to provide opportunities for ALL the folks of Saryrn who might not otherwise get a chance. And, for the most part, I think we've done a fair amount to keep things this way, though we may not have been perfect.<br>
<br>
I'm not disagreeing with you, as I've noticed some of the same tendancies, but I'd like to put forth a couple of reasons why things might be a little more &quot;elitist&quot; right now...<br>
<br>
Training process - From discussion I've seen in the past, a majority of the reason why people have been suggesting SGA only events is for the training. One prevailing attitude is that we need to work together well, and become a cohesive team before we offer our services to everyone else. I believe the idea is that we won't do anyone else much good until we can get our own act together.<br>
<br>
Logistics - Since up until relatively recently, there's been no solid management of things, we really havn't had a decent way of getting organized on our own, nevermind for the non-SGA folks. <br>
<br>
With that said...<br>
<br>
Now that things are solidifying, IMO it's time that we make sure that we set down some good habits and make sure we don't fall into the UberGuild realm. <br>
<br>
Perhaps we should start bringing in folks from other guilds, or advertising our bigger raids on the Saryrn board...I'm not sure. But I think Hareq's pointed out a dangerous trend that's started that, if we're not careful, might turn into something we really would rather not have around. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzalliben.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zalliben</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/16/01 9:29:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: State of the Union address</span><hr size=1> Bam Bam is the official mouthpiece so I'll let his words be the official responce. But I'll give my .02 worth since I'm an opinionated loudmouth.<br>
<br>
The ONLY times someone should not roll on a piece of gear they can use is a) a person has geared the  raid towards getting that particualar item or b) they already have the item (or something better).<br>
<br>
The ONLY times someone should get the boot from a group is a) their conduct is poor or b) they are told from the begining that they are holding a spot for an enroute friend. Even then that is questionable.<br>
<br>
I'm not going to comment on the other guilds portion. I'll let Bamil do that one <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukrytogspiritwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krytog Spiritwalker</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/16/01 10:01:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: State of the Union address</span><hr size=1> I concur that such actions are unacceptable, period. So long as the inviduals who join on any raids agree to need before greed philosphy, looting rights is a mute point. Surely some of the ppl who read this board know who was at fault so they have the opportunity to explain any reasons behind the actions. Every story has two sides.  This does not sound like any of the upper lvls I have grouped with thus far in the SGA and I am very curious as to who has adopted such an attitude.<br>
<br>
While there are many SGA only groups it is more out of new friendships forming than attempts to block out non-SGA comrades. IMHO.<br>
<br>
Krytog Spiritwalker - Proclaimers of Justice <p>Ask of the Spirits and the way will be shown...</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukrytogspiritwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krytog Spiritwalker</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10> at: 4/16/01 10:04:44 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Olavf Phyrefist</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/16/01 11:46:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> /Nods  (nt)</span><hr size=1> . <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzenknight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zenknight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/16/01 11:48:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: State of the Union address</span><hr size=1> Well I'm curious as to when this took place and WHY I WASN'T INVITED TO ICEWELL. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Every Icewell raid that we have done to date has been thus, need before greed. if you need the spell or piece of armor great if no one needs (spells) then we split them up and donated back to the guilds, meaning spells to each rep there of the SGA guids and guests like isengard.<br>
<br>
Now as far as the SGA only raids go. If I do a gear camp like GEBS your damn right it's SGA only. I do not feel the need to waste my time and all the others on the gear camp to outfit some guy who happened to be sitting at the zone wanting to go. Who's guild would not reciprocate in kind. If the turn out is good from our casters then so be it. Icewell has been different and I have worked hand in hand with other guild such as Isengard and Familjen to supply all who needed with armor and spells.<br>
<br>
The planes. Hate was a good example of this. We post weeks in advance to go and we get 1 SGA cleric, 1 FD puller and no rouges. We invited 2 extra clerics to go with us that were non SGA. The moment it got ugly one of the clerics (non SGA) threatened to leave before the CR was done. I personally would rather have people with me in key postions that have a vested interest in us getting out of a sticky stiuation then bailing cause they don't like something.<br>
<br>
Now I understand you points Hareq, Krytog and Zalliben. Consider this, it's all well and good to take friends along with us on raids, it's another thing entirely to take a horde of people that just decided they want a shot at loot and don't know how to raid into fear causing us heartache. A few friends is fine but how do you determine who is their for loot only and won't cause problems? Where is the cut off point as to who get's loot from an SGA raid. Do we take 20 extra people 10 extra? Is it fair to the members of the SGA to have to roll with 5 other Rangers who just showed up that day and won't be back after they get what they want?<br>
<br>
I don't see the SGA as a means to let the hordes of Norrath into large encounters. We go to the planes and gear camps to outfit our members not every Joe Blow that decides hey this is my shot at uber loot. Do we take friends sure we know them, group with them and trust them. Do we take everyone that wants to go, Hell no, if another small guild wants to go to the planes regularly with us then JOIN THE SGA!!!<br>
<br>
<br>
Zen <p>Zenknight Darkhorse,
52 Champion,
Warlord ,
Screaming Fist</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukrytogspiritwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krytog Spiritwalker</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/16/01 12:04:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: State of the Union address</span><hr size=1> I agree for the most part Zen. However, if we require additional ppl just to do the camp then they deserve a shot at the drops also and need to know the loot rules up front so they can decide if they want to participate.<br>
<br>
There are several guild wanting to join the SGA currently that help out on some of the raids.  Some of them will probably join us just as soon was we get all the detail ironed out and start adding additional guilds.<br>
<br>
I do find it strange that they are starting to have icewell raids without you since you finally have all but given up in frustration...  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Ask of the Spirits and the way will be shown...</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzenknight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zenknight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/16/01 12:10:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: State of the Union address</span><hr size=1> Actually I do remeber this incident the more I think about it. The spell in question was a cleric spell and this raid in Icewell was mine. Cicotte, Lingling, Zombei and a few others were there. This person wanted to roll on all the spells. He was interested in cash loot not his (druid) spell drops. I informed him that if he didn't need the spell (which he did not) that the spells were being donated back to the guilds there.<br>
<br>
He left of his own accord with the comment well then you don't need me. He was not kicked out by a cleric, in fact his leaving made Ling's life alot harder and she had to try and heal both groups and died in the process. He had replaced Mennian who had to log. <br>
<br>
So for the record the druid is full of @#%$!<br>
<br>
No one asked this knuckle head to leave so that he could be replaced by a cleric.<br>
<br>
The drop in question was a cleric spell Celestial Healing.<br>
<br>
Once he realized that cash loot was not an option he bailed.<br>
<br>
If you doubt the story then by all means ask the others.<br>
<br>
So next time you get a story like this from some loot hungry player out for himself please take the time to ask us first before you post a glowing indictment. It's obvious who was in Icewell and I think you know us a little better then that.<br>
<br>
Zen <p>Zenknight Darkhorse,
52 Champion,
Warlord ,
Screaming Fist</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uhareq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hareq</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/16/01 12:43:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: State of the Union address</span><hr size=1> I'm glad to get another side of the story, you can understand that I'm caught between friends in game and friends out of game, but I have to disagree with you on your cash loot point.<br>
<br>
If other people are invited into your group/raid, then they are entitled to roll on loot.  This just seems like common sense.<br>
<br>
 <p>Hareq Ghoulslayer, 54 Paladin of Amnesty, Saryrn
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukrytogspiritwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krytog Spiritwalker</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/16/01 12:58:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: State of the Union address</span><hr size=1> If it's an item that would go to the coffers then a represenative from each guild present (even Non-SGA) should have a chance to get the item for their guild also. If the person is non-guilded then they would have a chance at it also. It would not be fair to penalize for not being in a guild nor for being a non-SGA guild participating in an SGA event. Unfortunately, there are ppl who play only to get loot and as we identify them they may or may not be on the top of the list of ppl to invite when we are looking for people. Leaders who are running any raids should be very clear to anyone outside the SGA regarding how the loot will be distributed for anything that is not needed by a raid person.<br>
 (THESE ARE PERSONAL OPINIONS) <p>Ask of the Spirits and the way will be shown...</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzenknight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zenknight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/16/01 2:25:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: State of the Union address</span><hr size=1> Ok more to the point this is not about cash loot this is about a Bull @#%$. The story as told in the first post is blatantly incorrect. <br>
<br>
No DRUID spell dropped that this friend of Hareq's was not allowed to roll on.<br>
<br>
He was NOT asked to leave so a SGA cleric could replace him.<br>
In fact he replaced the only SGA cleric that showed that night.<br>
<br>
He left when he found out that we were not rolling on cash loot and was quite flip about being only there for loot.<br>
<br>
Now if any of you want to debate those points fine but frankly I really don't care what the common sense thing to do 3 weeks ago was. Those were the loot rules at that time on that raid and have sense changed. If you don't like that sorry you weren't there. The raid was an all SGA raid until Mennian left and we did agree to the loot rules by virtue of my posts to have the raid on this board. <br>
<br>
I tell you though defending this subject by saying well the loot rules should have been different in hind sight is pretty dam weak. The guy said we screwed him and dumped him not that he objected to the loot rules and left which is what happened.<br>
<br>
This is not the Blast Furnace but it's starting to look like it.<br>
<br>
If you guys have such an issue with this fine then count me out, cause quite frankly my integretiy in life and in this game have never been in question because I make sure not to step on people and to be ethical.<br>
<br>
Thanks for pissing me off<br>
Zen <p>Zenknight Darkhorse,
52 Champion,
Warlord ,
Screaming Fist</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> CaladanieWyndwalker</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/16/01 3:37:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Icewell spell</span><hr size=1> <br>
<br>
I am dont normally speak out against others unless I see a obivious wrong in the works. I was present on this Icewell raid with Zenknight. I remember it well cause it was the first time I had ever been on a high end raid and I got summoned by one of the ice midgets. Anyway Zenknight is completely right in his statement &quot;No Druid spells dropped that night&quot;. We did however get a Celestial Healing spell, a couple of mage spells and one wizzie spell. And since noone at the raid could use the cleric spell it went to one of the SGA guilds for a cleric that could use it. At the point when the spell dropped our cleric had left and the druid had only just joined us a pull or so before it dropped. After the spell dropped and we didnt roll on it, since no one present could use it, He did disband and as i recall that was one of the last pulls as it left us with just Lingling as the healer. This resulted in about 3 or 4 deaths(one of which was Lingling). The raid then ended as the suriving hand full of us worked to get the folks an Exp Rez.<br>
