Proclaimers of Justice <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utildaienskywolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tildaien Skywolf</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10> at: 4/16/01 5:16:47 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bsaryrnguildallianceboard.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=tekkang>Tekkang</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>GM of Spirit Guardians</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/16/01 8:44:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: state of the union address</span><hr size=1> Regardless of what happenned this is old news.<br>
<br>
This is not a flame and nothing to flame over.<br>
<br>
We need to draft concrete loot rules into the charter to prevent confusion from happenning again.<br>
<br>
-Tekkang <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umyriahwind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Myriahwind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/17/01 6:34:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: state of the union address</span><hr size=1> First; yes we need firmer loot rules.<br>
<br>
Second; we need to give the raid leader the benefit of the doubt. It is a very hard job to do. Sometimes it is not obvious why the raid leader is doing something, and we better be well informed before we blast him for his decisions. (Obviously I am at fault for doing this before, sorry)<br>
<br>
Third; I am a little concerned about the attitude &quot;SGA only.&quot; For instant on planes raids I think we should allow friends to attend, but that friend should have a sponsor who will be held responsible for their friends behavior. One person can kill everyone on a planes raid; so we need to be picky about who joins the raids. We also need some sort of rule about joining in the middle of a raid. Purely equipment raids like the GEBs raid are different. Everyone in such a raid should know and be reminded that the raid is to get an SGA member a certain item or items. Most high level people are aware of such things, but reminders help prevent hard feelings.<br>
<br>
Fourth; the raid leader cant do everything. It think we all should make sure the group we are in knows what is going on. For instance, after the raid leader explains how we are attacking hate, someone in out group should say; &quot;so we all camo up, zone in when BEN says GO, and then run straight in until we see fire wall and then head to the zone wall just to the left of the fire wall?&quot;  &quot; and if we get attacked we run a little to the left and die?&quot; (or whatever the instructions were) Then make sure our group members all respond; yes! I believe it is the responsibility of everyone in a group to make sure their group knows what is up.  So we if move, everyone in the group should be saying; &quot;were moving guys, follow Hareq to the east.&quot;  And when someone new joins a group make sure they know the loot rules. In the case that started this thread I think the members of the raid let Zenknight down a bit by not explaining the loot rules to tht druid; although I guess from what Cicotte said there was not really much time to explain.<br>
<br>
Myriah (Not trying to flame anyone, just think we should talk this all out and come to some agreement.) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utelivaksk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TelivakSK</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/17/01 7:21:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Large scale raids</span><hr size=1> When SGA host large scale raids(24+ people), SGA members and friends of the SGA that were invited should be the only ones that are allowed to attend freely.  Which means, NOT just everyone who felt like showing up that so and so day can join us, provided that we are not lacking the key classes(Cleric, chanter) of course.  I don't see why SGA has to host a so called &quot;completely open raid&quot;.  It's a ridiculous notion.  Since when did any raid composed of 40+ people organized?  Since when did any raid composed of 40+ people considered fair?  <br>
<br>
Has people forgotten that certain PoF raid when people started to show up 4 hours into the raid just for loot and when Arch FDed and ninjaed that Umbral BP while everyone else went down fighting?  Loot, like it or not, is an aspect of the game.  How many SGA members you know will show up raid after raid if non-SGA members keep getting lucky and winning all the good items?  Hypothetically speaking, if you have 20 SGA member and 10 non-SGA members present at a raid, and the 10 non-SGA members end up winning 3/4 of the loot due to lucky rolls, how is that considered to be &quot;taking care of our own&quot;?  <br>
<br>
Yeah I know some of you may think that I'm getting close to the &quot;uber guild mentality&quot; but you know what, these are all perfectly valid points.  SGA, like any other guild entity, should exist to benefit its member.  Diplomacy and good relations with others is important but it shouldn't come at the expense of SGA members.  While &quot;SGA only raids&quot; may not be the thing for us to do, &quot;invite only raids&quot; should be.  After all, we have been, and always will invite those players who are friends of SGA to the raids.  <br>
<br>
One last item.  Everyone who have been to their share of large raids should know by now that &quot;open raids&quot; are;<br>
<br>
1. A good deal of the time, they are unorganized and end in disaster.<br>
2. Shady characters tend to show up and end up ruining the experience for others.<br>
3. Too many chiefs, not enough indians.<br>
4. Loot rules are rarely *acceptable* to everyone participating and of course, lots of complaints.<br>
<br>
These are the perfect arguements why NOT to have completely open raids. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utelivaksk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TelivakSK</A> at: 4/17/01 7:47:18 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uholtthecleric.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Holt the Cleric</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/17/01 9:23:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Large scale raids</span><hr size=1> After reading all these post I am getting quite worried about the stability of our Alliances. It is seeming that we are no longer friends grouping to achieve a common goal, but instead we are reaching the mentality of the uber guilds. I personally will not be a part of such a thing. I have played this game since beta and have seen SO many guilds disolve. It seems that everytime a guild or alliance fades it doesn't explode but instead implodes in on itself. I am sorry to see that the heads of the Alliance are in dispute here and that they cannot stand together in one common agreement as to the looting policy and the simple playing nice rules. I feel that I am standing on a hill watching an empire crumble under its own disputes. Please let us put this minor thing behind us and move on and become even a stronger Alliance. <br>
<br>
On a side note:<br>
I agree with hareq about the cookie cutter responses from other guilds wanting to join the SGA. simple fact is we could use more people to some of the larger scale raids such as the planes.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzalliben.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zalliben</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/17/01 9:55:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: State of the Union address</span><hr size=1> I don't think it's as much a disagreement as an exchange of ideas. I don't think the loot policy was ever really covered the idea of a non-SGA person in the group. Probably just an oversight.<br>
<br>
In terms of loot disbursement, I'm all for making sure people aren't inherently excluded from loot, provided the need before greed rules are met, and if the raid is generated to get a specific person an item (epic or otherwise).<br>
<br>
Here's a version of how this could have gone.<br>
<br>
Let's say the following people are in a group. Myself (Necro), Malleolus (Wizard) and Holt (Cleric). We are all SGA members. We zone in and UnguildedDruid wants to join ans we agree. The SGA members are in agreement that any spell drops deemed excess will be donated to their guilds coffers. But what about UnguildedDruid? Does he or doesn't he get a chance for the &quot;excess&quot; spell. My vote is yes. Here's how this could have gone.<br>
<br>
First spell drop is &quot;Celestial Healing&quot; and Holt doesn't have it so he gets it. Second spell drop is Translocate, but Mall already has it. A representative from each guild and unguilded Druid roll for it. Unguilded Druid wins the roll and receives the spell. Keep in mind a good chunk of the spell auctions I've seen have been one spell for another. So why shouldn't the Druid be able to trade a spell for it. Or sell it for all he cares. The fact is that regardless of it being an SGA raid, people who aren't in a guild should get a chance at something provided it has passed the NEED BEFORE GREED policy. My opinion is if we keep something away from someone who is a member of a pick up group we have shown the following:<br>
<br>
1- We are a bunch of elitist SOB's<br>
2- Since we are elitist SOB's why would you want to join the SGA or a guild in it?<br>
<br>
Keeping a drop internal to the SGA (once it has passed the NBG filter) IMHO is like having a lolipop at the playground none of your friends want (they hate chocolate) but keeping it from a kid who might be able to trade the cholocolate for a cherrry.<br>
<br>
I'm all for allowing non SGA people on raids. If someone behaves poorly they don't get asked back again. It is my hope we can avoid making the SGA an Uberguild. We all have to learn how to do planes at some point. Inviting someone we don't know on a raid shows an act of kindness that will be repaid later. Either from them inviting you on a raid or helping you out. Sure, there are going to be times when the raid is just plain full. <br>
<br>
It's a game. Why can't we have fun and get along with everyone, regardless of if they are in the SGA or not?<br>
<br>
If we die, we die. It's a given we are going to die in this game at least another 20 times. What's one more <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utelivaksk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TelivakSK</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/17/01 9:55:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Large scale raids</span><hr size=1> Well, call it uber guild mentality if you will but completely open plane raids is just asking for trouble in my opinion.  Open dragon raids are different because old world dragons are relatively easy and is at most, a 3 hour encounter with maybe an hour of actual fighting involved.  When I go on a long, drawn out, large scale raid, I would like to go with people I trust and can depend on.  That's the common ground between all guilds, large and small. <br>
<br>
You shouldn't have to tell people the simpliest of instructions like mezz/root the adds, mana pump the healers.. etc, during these raids.  They should know it already.  That's the problem with completely open raids, so many people show up whom you've never seen or played with before.  You don't know if they know their class.  You don't know if they're capable of dealing with the pressure.  Even more so, and I've seen this many times, some people just don't contribute.  Some players just sit around and don't offer any useful assistance to the raid, while just simply expecting to get to roll on loots.<br>
<br>
Sorry, I will no longer participate in any un-moderated, &quot;completely open&quot; plane raids because the probability of that raid succeeding is 50/50 at best with the new changes to planes in place.  I certainly do not feeling like going on a 6+ hour CR.  Just look at the past few open plane raids.  Didn't H&amp;E had to rescue corpses from both PoF and PoH just a week and half ago? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uholtthecleric.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Holt the Cleric</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(4/17/01 10:17:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=151.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: State of the Union address</span><hr size=1> As far as open raids go I will no longer even group with non-SGA members if I don't have at least one other SGA in the group with me. I agree with Telivak in the simple fact that SGA members we hope are more loyal to the cause than just some guy that was picked up to farm phatz l3Wtt for his self or to fatten his pockets. Just this past weekend I have had horrible experiences in not grouping with SGA members. I ended up having to res an entire guild in Kedge because the thrown together group didn't know how to interact with each other.<br>
<br>
A thing that I have noticed more and more are high level newbies. I am so tired of seeing someone simply now know how to play there class. They were either Power Leveled up and don't know the role they are suppose to play or they found a nice static spawn to level off of. For an example I saw a level 47 cleric in Karnors and he was actually attempting to meelee the dogs with his uber hammer. I just watched helplessly as his group members died one bby one as he nuked and hammered the dogs. I of course ressed them all he was removed from the group and I was his replacement. &gt;<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <br>
<br>
Back to the point:<br>
If we are to learn to interact with each other and learn to take up in each others weaknesses and be a strong alliance of guilds then I think we should have SGA raids in which there are SGA groups and loot goes to SGA members. <br>
<br>
But, in the same respect I think that the SGA needs to gain a good reputation for allowing people to come to its raids and that we have a good group of people that will help others and have the Need before Greed looting policy. <br>
<br>
Loot to me is nothing really. Granted I do want to be all purple, but I have played since beta and I got one helm of purple to show for it ... I can wait <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
